Configuring Apache

-Stored in plain text files
-Typically named httpd.conf
-Location set at compile time
	 Possible to override
-Changes only recognized when started  i.e graceful

Configuration Location

-Can include additional configurations from main
-Different distributions have different locations, structure

Apache Config by distribution

Fedora and CentOS /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf
 one monolithic file
Debian and Ubuntu /etc/apache2/apache2.conf
 	Related, smaller configuration files
 	One per site
 	One per group of configuration

Finding the Apache Configuration
 -Start with default location in distribution
 -apachectl can describe the default configurations of files
 -Search the entire file system
 
http://httpd.apache.org/docs/current/configuring.html

